while you watch.

241
00:09:22.436 --> 00:09:23.563
This shit gets complicated.

242
00:09:23.646 --> 00:09:25.356
Not that. Um…

243
00:09:26.357 --> 00:09:27.608
We're getting Tommy White.

244
00:09:27.692 --> 00:09:29.944
[exhales] But he's a point guard. [grunts]

245
00:09:30.778 --> 00:09:31.779
Yeah.

246
00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:33.573
Wait a minute.

247
00:09:35.283 --> 00:09:36.909
Are you trading me?

248
00:09:37.410 --> 00:09:39.662
What? No. no. They don't want you.

249
00:09:39.745 --> 00:09:42.498
I mean. they didn't ask about you.
We're keeping you.

250
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:44.250
We love you. man.

251
00:09:44.333 --> 00:09:48.879
Okay. so I'll still be the starter.
and he'll come off the bench. right?

252
00:09:48.963 --> 00:09:52.592
Yeah. well. he'll come off the bench
when they announce him as a starter.

253
00:09:52.675 --> 00:09:55.386
and you'll start playing
later in the game.

254
00:09:55.469 --> 00:09:58.014
In… in my eyes. you guys are equals.

255
00:09:58.097 --> 00:09:59.432
-Oh. equal?
-Mm-hmm.

256
00:09:59.515 --> 00:10:01.684
Okay. so we're like worth
the same. then. right?

257
00:10:01.767 --> 00:10:03.394
Well. sure.

258
00:10:03.477 --> 00:10:04.478
All right. [exhales]

259
00:10:06.606 --> 00:10:07.690
See you later.

260
00:10:07.773 --> 00:10:08.608
[snaps fingers] Yeah.

261
00:10:10.067 --> 00:10:12.445
All right.
I'm gonna go ahead and burn this out.

262
00:10:13.487 --> 00:10:14.530
[grunts]

263
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:15.573
-Come on.
-[snapping]

264
00:10:15.656 --> 00:10:17.033
Oh!

265
00:10:18.117 --> 00:10:19.285
[hip-hop music playing]

266
00:10:19.368 --> 00:10:20.411
[Ness groans]

267
00:10:21.245 --> 00:10:23.372
♪ I'mma turn this floor
Into a dance floor ♪

268
00:10:23.456 --> 00:10:25.499
♪ Get up out your seat
I need your hands up ♪

269
00:10:25.583 --> 00:10:27.752
♪ Need to see you move
What you in the chair for? ♪

270
00:10:28.461 --> 00:10:30.046
[indistinct chatter]

271
00:10:30.129 --> 00:10:31.005
[man] In the city?

272
00:10:33.132 --> 00:10:34.133
[quietly] Shit.

273
00:10:35.301 --> 00:10:37.345
[quietly] Shit. Shit. Jackie.

274
00:10:38.012 --> 00:10:39.597
[quietly] Jackie.

275
00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:41.140
What the hell?

276
00:10:41.724 --> 00:10:43.476
How could you not tell me Jay is here?

277
00:10:43.559 --> 00:10:46.062
Since you were getting a spray tan
and he's not on your schedule.

278
00:10:46.145 --> 00:10:47.772
-I thought you wouldn't see him.
-Oh God.

279
00:10:47.855 --> 00:10:49.815
All the walls in this place
are made of glass.

280
00:10:49.899 --> 00:10:51.108
Of course I'm gonna see him.

281
00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:54.445
and I'm covered
in vanilla celebration cake.

282
00:10:54.528 --> 00:10:56.906
I think he wants to say "hi" to everyone.

283
00:10:56.989 --> 00:10:58.074
Well. if he comes in here.

284
00:10:58.157 --> 00:11:02.036
you tell him I'm at a luncheon.
and it's a panel for women in sports.

285
00:11:02.119 --> 00:11:04.914
and… and… and it's moderated
by Barbara Walters.

286
00:11:04.997 --> 00:11:06.791
I'm pretty sure she's not with us anymore.

287
00:11:06.874 --> 00:11:08.250
-What?
-Yeah.

288
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:09.293
-When?
-[knock on door]

289
00:11:09.377 --> 00:11:10.378
Hey.

290
00:11:11.045 --> 00:11:13.172
-Hi.
-What up. Jackie?

291
00:11:13.255 --> 00:11:15.383
-Jay. hi. Oh.
-[Jay] Hey.

292
00:11:16.425 --> 00:11:17.259
Oh.

293
00:11:17.968 --> 00:11:21.013
Oh. uh. that was actually there
when you walked in. I…

294
00:11:21.597 --> 00:11:24.600
I'm sorry I couldn't get a hang
on the books. Um…

295
00:11:24.684 --> 00:11:26.560
[smacks lips] It's been
a pretty crazy week.

296
00:11:26.644 --> 00:11:28.312
Oh. 'cause of Tommy White?

297
00:11:29.105 --> 00:11:31.607
-Yeah. Ness told me. [laughs]
-God. Damn it. Ness.

298
00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:33.442
Don't worry. I. uh… I won't say anything.

299
00:11:33.526 --> 00:11:35.194
-He made me pinky swear.
-Mmm.

300
00:11:35.277 --> 00:11:36.445
Look. it'll be huge for you guys.

301
00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:38.906
He's the perfect guard you need
for your five-out offense.

302
00:11:38.989 --> 00:11:43.369
Right? And he's big enough on defense.
he can play our switch-heavy scheme.

303
00:11:43.452 --> 00:11:44.787
And he's also a knockdown shooter.

304
00:11:44.870 --> 00:11:46.831
Yeah. I know.
We could get that ring with him.

305
00:11:46.914 --> 00:11:48.999
Winning is all that really matters.
all right?

306
00:11:49.083 --> 00:11:51.210
-Don't worry about the ring.
-Says the guy with three.

307
00:11:51.293 --> 00:11:52.211
[softly] Three.

308
00:11:52.294 --> 00:11:53.129
[chuckles quietly]

309
00:11:55.172 --> 00:11:58.050
Hey. uh. would you wanna grab dinner
tonight after the game?

310
00:11:58.634 --> 00:11:59.593
Oh. I can't.

311
00:11:59.677 --> 00:12:02.930
I have a rehearsal dinner… for my wedding.

312
00:12:03.013 --> 00:12:05.558
I'm… I'm. um… getting married tomorrow.

313
00:12:05.641 --> 00:12:06.851
Oh. wow.

314
00:12:06.934 --> 00:12:08.352
Of course. yeah.

315
00:12:08.436 --> 00:12:09.687
Yeah. of course.

316
00:12:10.187 --> 00:12:11.021
[scoffs]

317
00:12:12.189 --> 00:12:13.441
Uh. so no invite.

318
00:12:15.943 --> 00:12:17.611
Okay. Well. um…

319
00:12:18.612 --> 00:12:19.947
Hey. congratulations.

320
00:12:20.781 --> 00:12:24.368
Actually. you know what? Um. I want you to
keep the rest of your tan.

321
00:12:24.452 --> 00:12:25.703
[exhales] Well. thank you.

322
00:12:28.748 --> 00:12:30.124
Anyway. I'm really happy for you.

323
00:12:30.207 --> 00:12:31.459
[tender music playing]

324
00:12:31.542 --> 00:12:32.543
And Lev.

325
00:12:35.671 --> 00:12:36.839
[exhales]

326
00:12:38.466 --> 00:12:41.677
No. are you serious?
Andrew. come on. we had a deal.

327
00:12:41.761 --> 00:12:43.846
Why are you doing this to me?

328
00:12:43.929 --> 00:12:45.347
Andrew… [splutters]

329
00:12:45.431 --> 00:12:46.307
Hello?

330
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.602
-Hello?
-[line disconnects]

331
00:12:50.186 --> 00:12:51.228
Everything okay?

332
00:12:52.354 --> 00:12:53.939
The deal is dead.

333
00:12:54.023 --> 00:12:57.026
Nashville used me
to get a better offer for Tommy White.

334
00:12:57.526 --> 00:12:58.360
I got played.

335
00:12:58.444 --> 00:13:00.529
That explains why I just got off the phone
with Travis's agent.

336
00:13:00.613 --> 00:13:02.490
Oh no. What does he want?

337
00:13:02.573 --> 00:13:04.867
He said you promised Travis
the same deal as Tommy?

338
00:13:04.950 --> 00:13:07.495
He Jedi mind-fucked me
like the Nashville GM.

339
00:13:07.578 --> 00:13:08.871
Why is everybody so smart?

340
00:13:08.954 --> 00:13:10.873
The family was right about me.

341
00:13:10.956 --> 00:13:12.416
Listen. blood oath.

342
00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:14.126
-Oh…
-We never tell anybody this happened.

343
00:13:14.210 --> 00:13:15.169
-Hey.
-Give me your hand.

344
00:13:15.252 --> 00:13:17.797
-What is… Ness. what's wrong with you?
-I'm gonna cut you first.

345
00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:20.925
You need to calm down.
Okay. the fact is. you blew it.

346
00:13:21.008 --> 00:13:22.092
Robinson used you.

347
00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:25.596
All you can do is man up
and figure out the next best move.

348
00:13:26.305 --> 00:13:27.181
Okay?

349
00:13:29.016 --> 00:13:29.975
Okay.

350
00:13:30.059 --> 00:13:31.143
Thank you. Ali.

351
00:13:33.395 --> 00:13:34.480
I'll see you later.

352
00:13:36.649 --> 00:13:38.651
[engine running]

353
00:13:44.198 --> 00:13:45.324
Ness. what are you doing?

354
00:13:45.825 --> 00:13:47.409
You should leave. brother.

355
00:13:47.493 --> 00:13:49.495
It's not safe for you in this car.

356
00:13:50.079 --> 00:13:52.665
Any moment.
the fumes are gonna overtake me.

357
00:13:52.748 --> 00:13:54.208
[breathes deeply]

358
00:13:54.291 --> 00:13:56.418
Do you think
you're trying to kill yourself?

359
00:13:56.919 --> 00:13:58.712
'Cause you got the AC on full blast.

360
00:13:58.796 --> 00:14:01.507
You have to be in an enclosed space.
so the carbon monoxide…

361
00:14:02.007 --> 00:14:03.759
You know what? Why am I telling you this?

362
00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:05.219
[sighs] Oh God.

363
00:14:09.181 --> 00:14:11.642
-What's going on?
-I blew the Tommy White deal.

364
00:14:12.142 --> 00:14:14.436
-[sighs]
-[sobbing] Oh God.

365
00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:15.437
Jesus.

366
00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:19.316
I should just go back
to the Filipino prison.

367
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:20.693
-It wasn't that bad.
-Oh.

368
00:14:20.776 --> 00:14:23.988
We were like two weeks away from finishing
the "Smooth Criminal" dance.

369
00:14:24.071 --> 00:14:25.614
-[exhales]
-On top of that.

370
00:14:26.198 --> 00:14:28.701
I'm pretty sure
we owe Travis a big new contract.

371
00:14:28.784 --> 00:14:31.370
-Why?
-Because when I told him the Tommy news.

372
00:14:31.453 --> 00:14:32.997
I didn't want him to be mad at me.

373
00:14:33.080 --> 00:14:36.083
You can't make everyone happy
all of the time.

374
00:14:36.166 --> 00:14:38.752
Do you know who the least popular
person at this organization is?

375
00:14:38.836 --> 00:14:40.629
-It's me.
-Yeah. I was gonna say you.

376
00:14:40.713 --> 00:14:43.299
And that's because I don't care
if people like me.

377
00:14:43.382 --> 00:14:46.719
That's also probably why
you can't be in a long-term relationship.

378
00:14:46.802 --> 00:14:52.182
Yes. Look. don't let Isla
and Cam and Travis walk all over you.

379
00:14:53.058 --> 00:14:56.270
They don't need to like you.
but they need to respect you.

380
00:14:59.398 --> 00:15:00.816
Yeah. [sniffles]

381
00:15:03.402 --> 00:15:05.237
[quirky music playing]

382
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:07.364
Thank you. Sandy. I love you.

383
00:15:07.448 --> 00:15:08.449
I love you too.

384
00:15:09.491 --> 00:15:10.743
♪ If you need a friend… ♪

385
00:15:10.826 --> 00:15:14.580
-See you at the rehearsal dinner. okay?
-Hey. no. no. no. that's…

386
00:15:14.663 --> 00:15:16.874
-I'm gonna fix this!
-No!

387
00:15:16.957 --> 00:15:18.876
You're blocking me in.

388
00:15:21.295 --> 00:15:23.422
[Lev] I can't believe
this night is finally here.

389
00:15:23.505 --> 00:15:25.299
Hey. can I ask you something?

390
00:15:26.884 --> 00:15:28.677
-Is it about the zit stickers?
-[laughs]

391
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:30.054
-Law said…
-No.

392
00:15:30.137 --> 00:15:31.972
…my dress tomorrow will cover them.

393
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:37.311
It's not about the zit stickers.
It's. uh… about the prenup.

394
00:15:38.312 --> 00:15:41.523
Uncle Jack told me
he hasn't heard back on our counter.

395
00:15:41.607 --> 00:15:43.776
Yeah. my family's trying to figure it out.

396
00:15:47.154 --> 00:15:48.197
Your family?

397
00:15:50.282 --> 00:15:51.909
I thought you and I had figured it out.

398
00:15:51.992 --> 00:15:54.161
It's more complicated than that. Lev.

399
00:15:54.244 --> 00:15:57.289
There's a lot of factors.
It's not just about you and me.

400
00:15:57.373 --> 00:16:01.168
I… I mean. what happens if you die
and Ana de Armas takes over the Waves?

401
00:16:01.251 --> 00:16:02.711
What are you talking about?

402
00:16:02.795 --> 00:16:03.796
-Okay. Lev.
-Are you okay?

403
00:16:03.879 --> 00:16:07.091
Can you trust me.
and please just sign the original version?

404
00:16:07.174 --> 00:16:09.635
Why can't you trust me
and sign my version?

405
00:16:09.718 --> 00:16:12.137
'Cause it's not just about us.

406
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:14.848
My family needs certain protections.

407
00:16:16.058 --> 00:16:16.892
Oh.

408
00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:21.855
I didn't realize I was a threat.

409
00:16:23.524 --> 00:16:26.026
[R&B music playing]

410
00:16:31.573 --> 00:16:35.285
♪ For some time
I felt all alone ♪

411
00:16:35.786 --> 00:16:39.540
♪ But now. my baby's
Coming home to me ♪

412
00:16:39.623 --> 00:16:40.916
[light jazz music playing]

413
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:43.544
Look. Gene and I got in a huge fight
at our wedding too.

414
00:16:43.627 --> 00:16:45.671
Remember when his mom printed
all the menus in Korean.

415
00:16:45.754 --> 00:16:48.590
and my Thai relatives had to just eat
whatever they could pronounce?

416
00:16:48.674 --> 00:16:50.634
And you're still happily married.

417
00:16:50.718 --> 00:16:52.886
Exactly. I'm still married.

418
00:16:52.970 --> 00:16:54.263
Oh my God.

419
00:16:55.139 --> 00:16:57.641
What is my cousin Bennie doing here?

420
00:16:57.725 --> 00:17:00.561
Can I get a glass of vodka
and a glass of clear rum. please?

421
00:17:00.644 --> 00:17:01.603
-Yeah.
-It's free?

422
00:17:01.687 --> 00:17:03.313
-Free? Nice.
-Yeah. yeah.

423
00:17:03.397 --> 00:17:05.315
[Ali] Let's go before he sees us.

424
00:17:05.399 --> 00:17:07.026
Rumor is Tommy White's headed to New York.

425
00:17:07.109 --> 00:17:10.112
Where the fuck is Ness?
Too afraid to show his face around here.

426
00:17:10.195 --> 00:17:12.156
Just go easy on him. He feels bad enough.

427
00:17:12.239 --> 00:17:13.991
What up. cuzzies?

428
00:17:14.074 --> 00:17:17.745
-Open bar. pretty classy.
-There's always an open bar.

429
00:17:17.828 --> 00:17:20.748
Not at my second wedding.
Everyone got one drink ticket.

430
00:17:20.831 --> 00:17:22.374
That included Cokes too.

431
00:17:22.458 --> 00:17:24.668
Oh. hey. speaking of. do you have any. uh…

432
00:17:24.752 --> 00:17:27.254
-[sniffs]
-No. I don't. I'm sober now.

433
00:17:27.337 --> 00:17:29.298
Good. I didn't want any.

434
00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:30.591
[chuckling] Who's this guy?

435
00:17:30.674 --> 00:17:32.968
Cousin Bennie. Jackie.
Good to meet you. man.

436
00:17:33.052 --> 00:17:34.887
I actually met your mother
a long time ago.

437
00:17:34.970 --> 00:17:36.680
believe it or not. at the beach house.

438
00:17:36.764 --> 00:17:39.808
Looked exactly like Salma Hayek.
just smaller cans.

439
00:17:40.684 --> 00:17:41.643
How's Vegas. Bennie?

440
00:17:41.727 --> 00:17:44.188
Vegas is hot. my man. but good.

441
00:17:44.271 --> 00:17:47.066
I got a couple of businesses
I'm trying to get off the ground.

442
00:17:47.149 --> 00:17:49.568
But right now. what's keeping
the lights on is the RV Repo.

443
00:17:49.651 --> 00:17:50.861
It's a tough business.

444
00:17:50.944 --> 00:17:54.448
Like last week. I… I'm hauling away
this beautiful 2022 Dream Rider.

445
00:17:54.531 --> 00:17:56.450
We're going from Henderson to Tahoe.

446
00:17:56.533 --> 00:17:58.452
Halfway. along the way.
I hear like a bang.

447
00:17:58.535 --> 00:18:00.662
and I'm like. "Fuck. I got a flat."

448
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:02.247
So I pull over. I go in there.

449
00:18:02.331 --> 00:18:05.167
It was the owner.
He blew his brains out right around Zzyzx.

450
00:18:05.250 --> 00:18:06.085
-Jesus.
-Oh.

451
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:07.461
Happy ending.

452
00:18:08.003 --> 00:18:11.090
Police said he was a pedophile.
Justice. boom.

453
00:18:11.799 --> 00:18:12.633
Wow.

454
00:18:12.716 --> 00:18:14.885
I gotta go mingle with… other people.

455
00:18:14.968 --> 00:18:16.136
-Okay. that sounds good.
-Psst.

456
00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:19.139
Hey. who is that absolute dime
right there?

457
00:18:19.223 --> 00:18:20.265
That's my wife.

458
00:18:20.349 --> 00:18:21.642
[grimacing]

459
00:18:21.725 --> 00:18:22.601
-Sorry.
-Excuse me.

460
00:18:22.684 --> 00:18:24.770
I already told you
there's nobody sitting here.

461
00:18:24.853 --> 00:18:28.023
But if there's a place card.
I have to leave a meal. sir.

462
00:18:28.107 --> 00:18:31.235
No. it's fine. Put it down.
I… I'll be Charlie Cannoli. It's fine.

463
00:18:31.318 --> 00:18:33.737
Jesus Christ.
I've been trying to get food all night.

464
00:18:33.821 --> 00:18:36.865
-Mm. So what. did you get dumped?
-Yes.

465
00:18:37.533 --> 00:18:40.202
-Lizzy. Hi.
-Oh. congrats.

466
00:18:40.285 --> 00:18:42.329
-Oh.
-Or mazel tov. hey.

467
00:18:42.412 --> 00:18:43.956
-Yep. how are the kids?
-[chuckles]

468
00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:45.791
I don't know. Ask Cam.

469
00:18:45.874 --> 00:18:48.168
[laughing] Just kidding. Ask the nanny.

470
00:18:49.169 --> 00:18:51.130
-Can I ask you a question?
-Yes.

471
00:18:51.839 --> 00:18:53.048
Thank you.

472
00:18:53.132 --> 00:18:54.174
Um…

473
00:18:54.925 --> 00:18:56.760
How did you feel signing your prenup?

474
00:18:57.261 --> 00:19:00.556
Well. I was the fish tank girl
at the Standard Hotel.

475
00:19:00.639 --> 00:19:02.224
so I didn't really have much to lose.

476
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:04.226
So you weren't offended at all?

477
00:19:04.726 --> 00:19:06.520
I knew the family I was marrying into.

478
00:19:06.603 --> 00:19:09.022
and you cannot pretend
that marriage isn't a contract.

479
00:19:09.106 --> 00:19:09.940
It just is.

480
00:19:10.023 --> 00:19:11.650
Plus. it keeps you in line.

481
00:19:11.733 --> 00:19:13.026
What do you mean?

482
00:19:13.110 --> 00:19:15.821
Cam's got his vices. right? I've got mine.

483
00:19:16.321 --> 00:19:17.573
We need that structure.

484
00:19:17.656 --> 00:19:19.283
I mean. we can flirt
with doing bad things.

485
00:19:19.366 --> 00:19:21.034
I can flirt with my trainer
as much as I want.

486
00:19:21.118 --> 00:19:24.746
but I'm always gonna go back home to Cam
because of that contract.

487
00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:26.165
It's like a little string.

488
00:19:26.665 --> 00:19:27.583
Pulls us back.

489
00:19:27.666 --> 00:19:31.211
Yeah. but I don't think Lev and I have
anything to be pulled back from.

490
00:19:31.295 --> 00:19:33.255
Well. maybe not Lev. but… [chuckles]

491
00:19:33.755 --> 00:19:35.174
…you're a Gordon. right?

492
00:19:35.257 --> 00:19:36.800
There's probably something.

493
00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:39.553
I really gotta pee. I'll see you in a bit.

494
00:19:39.636 --> 00:19:41.638
[pensive music playing]

495
00:19:43.390 --> 00:19:46.310
-[glass clinking]
-[Isla chuckles]

496
00:19:46.393 --> 00:19:47.436
Hi.

497
00:19:47.936 --> 00:19:50.063
Good evening. everyone.
Thank you for coming.

498
00:19:50.147 --> 00:19:53.108
I know there's gonna be
a lot of speeches tomorrow.

499
00:19:53.192 --> 00:19:55.736
but I just wanted to say something.

500
00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:57.821
Since I've known Lev.

501
00:19:57.905 --> 00:20:03.744
I've been at a loss for words
to describe what a great man he is.

502
00:20:04.244 --> 00:20:07.289
In my family. we were raised
to assume everyone was out to get us.

503
00:20:07.372 --> 00:20:10.083
so we were taught.
question what the angle is.

504
00:20:10.167 --> 00:20:11.543
and how do I win?

505
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:15.631
But Lev. you definitely are not a Gordon.

506
00:20:16.381 --> 00:20:18.884
After almost a decade together.

507
00:20:19.384 --> 00:20:23.680
I have learned
that all Lev wants is to make me happy.

508
00:20:24.681 --> 00:20:28.143
And to have Friday night dinner
once a year with the squishy bread.

509
00:20:28.227 --> 00:20:30.187
-[all laugh]
-Shabbat.

510
00:20:30.270 --> 00:20:32.231
-All right.
-It should be once a week.

511
00:20:32.314 --> 00:20:34.650
-[crowd chuckling]
-[Isla] Yes. of course.

512
00:20:35.150 --> 00:20:36.193
Thank you. Linda.

513
00:20:36.276 --> 00:20:37.319
[all laugh]

514
00:20:37.402 --> 00:20:39.655
Lev is by far the best person I know.

515
00:20:40.656 --> 00:20:43.075
-His jawline is perfection.
-[all laugh]

516
00:20:43.158 --> 00:20:45.744
He sacrifices his body
on the pickleball court

517
00:20:45.827 --> 00:20:47.704
to make sure I do not get pelted.

518
00:20:47.788 --> 00:20:50.999
-I do.
-Every day. you make me a better person.

519
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:56.088
And I hope one day
I am good enough to deserve your love.

520
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:57.589
To Lev Levenson.

521
00:20:57.673 --> 00:20:58.590
[mouthing] I love you.

522
00:20:58.674 --> 00:21:00.092
-[man] Cheers.
-Cheers.

523
00:21:00.592 --> 00:21:03.512
-[glasses clinking]
-[people cheering. clapping]

524
00:21:07.224 --> 00:21:08.225
[softly] Thank you.

525
00:21:09.851 --> 00:21:11.395
Hey. [clears throat]

526
00:21:12.771 --> 00:21:14.648
-I've been thinking.
-I signed the prenup.

527
00:21:17.442 --> 00:21:21.071
I don't care what some… document says.

528
00:21:22.197 --> 00:21:24.491
I know
that we'll always take care of each other.

529
00:21:26.118 --> 00:21:28.120
[romantic music plays softly]

530
00:21:29.955 --> 00:21:31.206
[Cam] Hey. everybody.

531
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:34.710
You all may know me
as Isla's most attractive brother.

532
00:21:34.793 --> 00:21:35.877
and that would be accurate…

533
00:21:35.961 --> 00:21:36.878
[crowd chuckles]

534
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:39.089
…but I know I speak for the entire family

535
00:21:39.673 --> 00:21:42.551
when I say that we couldn't be happier
for our old gal.

536
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:47.681
Now. tomorrow's gonna be super Jewish.
and. um. I'm fine with that.

537
00:21:48.390 --> 00:21:51.560
but the Gordons are Scottish.

538
00:21:51.643 --> 00:21:55.981
A long time ago. the King of England
banned Scottish dancing.

539
00:21:56.064 --> 00:21:58.817
Now. that would be like
the President of the United States

540
00:21:58.900 --> 00:22:02.029
banning that little dance you guys do
in the circle where you lift the chair.

541
00:22:02.112 --> 00:22:03.488
The Hora.

542
00:22:03.572 --> 00:22:04.781
That's right. Linda.

543
00:22:05.407 --> 00:22:06.283
The horror.

544
00:22:06.366 --> 00:22:07.492
But tonight.

545
00:22:07.576 --> 00:22:09.119
deanamaid dannsa.

546
00:22:09.202 --> 00:22:12.122
which is Gaelic for "Let's dance."

547
00:22:12.205 --> 00:22:14.166
[bagpipe playing]

548
00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:16.585
-[crowd gasps]
-[Isla screams]

549
00:22:19.713 --> 00:22:20.922
[Isla] Oh…

550
00:22:21.631 --> 00:22:22.507
Wow.

551
00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:24.426
[bagpipes stop]

552
00:22:24.509 --> 00:22:26.887
[Scottish dance music playing]

553
00:22:26.970 --> 00:22:29.848
[crowd laughing. cheering]

554
00:22:31.224 --> 00:22:32.893
[Ali] Whoo! Whoo!

555
00:22:35.562 --> 00:22:37.564
[crowd clapping]

556
00:22:39.066 --> 00:22:40.692
-Unbelievable.
-[Isla laughs]

557
00:22:40.776 --> 00:22:43.487
-Un-frickin-believable.
-Oh. Bennie. Ew!

558
00:22:44.905 --> 00:22:46.907
[Scottish music continues]

559
00:22:49.868 --> 00:22:50.702
[Bennie] Oh my God.

560
00:23:03.006 --> 00:23:04.800
-Oh. can you believe it?
-It's so great.

561
00:23:04.883 --> 00:23:08.637
-[man] Yeah!
-[crowd applauds. cheers]

562
00:23:08.720 --> 00:23:10.722
[bagpipes resume]

563
00:23:12.224 --> 00:23:13.767
[bagpipes end]

564
00:23:13.850 --> 00:23:15.644
[all laughing]

565
00:23:15.727 --> 00:23:19.564
-And when you ripped your pants off. how?
-We went to Benson Boone's tailor.

566
00:23:19.648 --> 00:23:20.941
-[Isla] Oh.
-Hey.

567
00:23:21.024 --> 00:23:23.318
We're glad you made it.
even though you fucked up the trade.

568
00:23:23.402 --> 00:23:27.447
I'm still mad. but I will wait till Monday
to psychologically destroy you.

569
00:23:27.531 --> 00:23:30.617
No need. 'cause guess who just called in
the Tommy White trade

570
00:23:30.700 --> 00:23:31.660
at the league office.

571
00:23:32.828 --> 00:23:33.745
That's right.

572
00:23:33.829 --> 00:23:35.497
Tommy is officially a Wave.

573
00:23:35.580 --> 00:23:37.416
-[all] What?
-Wait. wait. you saved it?

574
00:23:37.499 --> 00:23:39.084
-Yeah.
-I thought Nashville was using you.

575
00:23:39.167 --> 00:23:42.003
They were. but in a pit of vipers.
you gotta become

576
00:23:42.963 --> 00:23:44.714
whatever eats a viper.

577
00:23:45.715 --> 00:23:49.386
Look. there was a rumor swirling
that Tommy White was going to New York.

578
00:23:49.469 --> 00:23:52.931
but I knew New York didn't have the pieces
to get the deal done on their own.

579
00:23:53.014 --> 00:23:56.184
So I had to figure out which teams
were doing the deal with New York.

580
00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:59.896
I called their GM Hale Thomas's office.
and I pretended to be his dad.

581
00:23:59.980 --> 00:24:02.732
I told him that I had fallen and I needed
to speak to him immediately.

582
00:24:02.816 --> 00:24:04.484
His assistant told me he'd checked in…

583
00:24:04.568 --> 00:24:05.402
Houston.

584
00:24:05.485 --> 00:24:07.404
…to the Four Seasons in Houston.

585
00:24:07.487 --> 00:24:08.989
That meant Houston was part of the trade.

586
00:24:09.072 --> 00:24:12.200
Then I remembered a rumor that
Houston had signed a deal with Charlotte.

587
00:24:12.284 --> 00:24:13.702
Monica. how do you spell Charlotte?

588
00:24:13.785 --> 00:24:16.621
Which meant that New York was just
gonna dump a bunch of salaries on him.

589
00:24:16.705 --> 00:24:17.789
So then what'd you do?

590
00:24:17.873 --> 00:24:20.375
I traded a bunch of late-round picks
and salary cap fillers

591
00:24:20.459 --> 00:24:22.002
to Houston and Charlotte.

592
00:24:22.085 --> 00:24:24.296
so that New York
couldn't fit Tommy White under the cap.

593
00:24:24.379 --> 00:24:26.298
Then I called Andrew Robinson in Nashville

594
00:24:26.381 --> 00:24:28.717
and told him
New York was off the table and hung up.

595
00:24:29.509 --> 00:24:33.305
Five minutes later. he called me back
practically begging us to take Tommy.

596
00:24:33.388 --> 00:24:34.222
So it's good?

597
00:24:34.306 --> 00:24:36.057
-Damn. bro.
-Yes!

598
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:37.767
-You're a god.
-[Sandy] Wow.

599
00:24:37.851 --> 00:24:40.020
The last thing I had to do
was break it to Travis.

600
00:24:40.103 --> 00:24:43.190
So I told Travis that he was going
to the bench. and we still valued him.

601
00:24:43.273 --> 00:24:44.900
If that meant he didn't like me. so be it.

602
00:24:44.983 --> 00:24:45.817
You have to take it.

603
00:24:45.901 --> 00:24:47.486
I was doing what's best for the team.

604
00:24:49.613 --> 00:24:51.323
I'm impressed. Ness.

605
00:24:52.574 --> 00:24:55.410
Well. thanks. Honestly.
that means a lot coming from you.

606
00:24:56.786 --> 00:24:59.831
One more thing. I don't want you guys
to use Ness as a verb anymore.

607
00:25:00.415 --> 00:25:03.376
It's demeaning and. quite honestly.
I'm… I'm better than that.

608
00:25:03.460 --> 00:25:04.794
[all gasp] Oh!

609
00:25:04.878 --> 00:25:06.463
-God. no!
-[Ali] Please. Ness!

610
00:25:06.546 --> 00:25:07.964
-Are you growing mushrooms?
-I'm out.

611
00:25:08.048 --> 00:25:09.466
We used to bathe together.

612
00:25:09.549 --> 00:25:10.717
[Ali] Oh God.

613
00:25:11.593 --> 00:25:13.512
Hi. here's what you're gonna do.

614
00:25:13.595 --> 00:25:17.057
You're gonna empty that water bottle
and fill it with four shots of vodka.

615
00:25:17.140 --> 00:25:18.058
You understand?

616
00:25:18.141 --> 00:25:19.100
Are you serious?

617
00:25:19.184 --> 00:25:20.101
You're right.

618
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:23.271
You're gonna empty that water bottle
and give me eight shots of vodka.

619
00:25:23.355 --> 00:25:25.357
[tense music playing]

620
00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:33.031
[Cam] Al. how's it going? Question mark.

621
00:25:34.699 --> 00:25:37.702
[Al] Congrats on Tommy White.
Team is gonna be awesome!

622
00:25:38.787 --> 00:25:42.499
[Cam] Totally. Hey. have you ever thought
about joining the team in a real way?

623
00:25:42.582 --> 00:25:44.334
Like a minority ownership?

624
00:25:49.589 --> 00:25:50.423
[phone buzzes]

625
00:26:10.318 --> 00:26:11.945
[tense music fades]

626
00:26:12.028 --> 00:26:13.863
[Isla exhales. yawns]

627
00:26:13.947 --> 00:26:16.700
All right. I'm gonna put all the gifts
in your guest bedroom.

628
00:26:16.783 --> 00:26:18.368
And when I leave. I'm taking the flowers.

629
00:26:18.451 --> 00:26:19.911
-You'll kill them.
-[Isla laughs]

630
00:26:20.620 --> 00:26:21.538
Oh.

631
00:26:21.621 --> 00:26:23.456
Oh!

632
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:25.041
[exhales]

633
00:26:25.834 --> 00:26:28.545
-Your DoorDash was outside.
-Bless you. Jackie.

634
00:26:28.628 --> 00:26:31.214
Also. I grabbed the groomsmen flashcards
from your desk.

635
00:26:31.298 --> 00:26:33.383
Damn. Lev has a lot of friends named Josh.

636
00:26:33.466 --> 00:26:35.677
-[Isla chuckles]
-Oh. I almost forgot.

637
00:26:35.760 --> 00:26:36.595
[zipper opens]

638
00:26:36.678 --> 00:26:39.055
This was on your desk.

639
00:26:39.764 --> 00:26:41.099
Mmm.

640
00:26:41.182 --> 00:26:42.976
Okay. that's it.

641
00:26:43.059 --> 00:26:45.604
-I will see you tomorrow at your wedding.
-Oh.

642
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:46.646
[kissing]

643
00:26:47.647 --> 00:26:48.940
-Bye. Jackie.
-Bye-bye.

644
00:26:52.027 --> 00:26:53.737
[exhales deeply]

645
00:26:54.321 --> 00:26:57.490
[Jay] This felt more like you
than anything on your registry.

646
00:26:57.574 --> 00:26:59.034
Now you have something borrowed.

647
00:27:00.952 --> 00:27:02.954
[sentimental music playing]

648
00:27:07.542 --> 00:27:08.543
[sighs]

649
00:27:18.428 --> 00:27:19.554
[smacks lips]

650
00:27:19.638 --> 00:27:20.639
[footsteps approaching]

651
00:27:20.722 --> 00:27:22.724
[Ali] I put an ice roller
on your bedside table.

652
00:27:22.807 --> 00:27:25.060
Please use it.
I love you. but you bag out. girl.

653
00:27:26.102 --> 00:27:27.395
-Hey. Ali.
-Hm?

654
00:27:28.271 --> 00:27:29.397
Um…

655
00:27:29.481 --> 00:27:31.524
Did you get nervous
the night before your wedding?

656
00:27:31.608 --> 00:27:34.611
Yes. and very drunk.

657
00:27:34.694 --> 00:27:36.029
[chuckles] I was 24.

658
00:27:36.613 --> 00:27:38.615
I didn't know what it meant to be married.

659
00:27:38.698 --> 00:27:40.617
but it was the thing I wanted most.

660
00:27:41.701 --> 00:27:43.370
-I love you.
-Yeah.

661
00:27:49.250 --> 00:27:50.585
[exhales]

662
00:27:54.172 --> 00:27:56.174
[sentimental music continues]

663
00:28:02.514 --> 00:28:04.516
[sentimental music fades]

664
00:28:08.436 --> 00:28:10.146
Oh. you're home early.

665
00:28:10.647 --> 00:28:12.023
Yeah. [clears throat]

666
00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:15.402
Noah did a shot of Malibu
and threw up on his Hokas.

667
00:28:15.485 --> 00:28:18.446
so… [chuckles]
…we thought we'd call it a night.

668
00:28:20.615 --> 00:28:21.908
[Lev grunts]

669
00:28:24.744 --> 00:28:26.705
Do you think
the prenup bothered you so much

670
00:28:26.788 --> 00:28:29.082
because deep down
you thought we wouldn't make it?

671
00:28:29.666 --> 00:28:30.750
What?

672
00:28:30.834 --> 00:28:32.168
No. why?

673
00:28:33.211 --> 00:28:34.212
[exhales deeply]

674
00:28:35.213 --> 00:28:37.757
And it will never bother you
that I didn't convert?

675
00:28:37.841 --> 00:28:40.135
-Why are you bringing this up?
-I don't know.

676
00:28:40.218 --> 00:28:45.807
[inhales] Lev. I don't…
I don't come home and… and think about

677
00:28:47.142 --> 00:28:49.561
my wedding dress
or walking down the aisle.

678
00:28:49.644 --> 00:28:50.478
[Lev sighs deeply]

679
00:28:50.562 --> 00:28:54.399
I'm thinking about
if Marcus has another season left in him

680
00:28:54.899 --> 00:28:56.693
or if we'll get the number one seed.

681
00:29:00.363 --> 00:29:04.409
I think you deserve someone
who loves you more than anything.

682
00:29:06.244 --> 00:29:07.245
[smacks lips]

683
00:29:08.496 --> 00:29:10.165
Isla. what are you telling me?

684
00:29:12.667 --> 00:29:13.835
[sighs deeply]

685
00:29:18.298 --> 00:29:19.883
Lev. I can't marry you.

686
00:29:22.552 --> 00:29:24.596
["Know Better"
by The Moonless Nights playing]

687
00:29:28.349 --> 00:29:30.935
♪ When there's no light ♪

688
00:29:31.019 --> 00:29:33.646
♪ It's a slow fight ♪

689
00:29:33.730 --> 00:29:39.611
♪ You got to keep trying
To hold your head high ♪

690
00:29:39.694 --> 00:29:42.030
♪ Still blue and ♪

691
00:29:42.113 --> 00:29:44.699
♪ Black hue and you ♪

692
